  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;necromancy;\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;cleric/oracle 2, medium 2, occultist 3, shaman 2, sorcerer/wizard 3, spiritualist 2, witch 2;\n    <strong>Domain</strong>&nbsp;Repose 2;\n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S, M/DF (salt and a copper piece for each of the corpse&#x27;s eyes)<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;corpse touched<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 day/level<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Will negates (object);&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>You preserve the remains of a dead creature so that they do not decay. Doing so effectively extends the time limit on raising that creature from the dead (see <i>raise dead</i>). Days spent under the influence of this spell don't count against the time limit.</p><p>Additionally, this spell makes transporting a slain (and thus decaying) comrade less unpleasant.</p><p>The spell also works on severed body parts and the like.</p>\n</div>\n",
